    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "@tararam - You should put the JAR and license file in a /lib folder that you add to your Eclipse CLASSPATH.  That&#39;ll take care of compile time and running inside Eclipse.  When you package and deploy your app, without Eclipse, you have to add that JAR to the CLASSPATH at runtime.  You can do this using -cp argument to java.exe OR use Maven to create an executable JAR with dependencies packaged inside it."
  } ],
